message.content: One of the most significant events that occurred in Norway in the past five years was the terrorist attack on Utøya Island and the government district of Oslo on July 22, 2011. This attack, carried out by a Norwegian right-wing extremist, resulted in the deaths of 77 people, mostly young participants attending a political youth camp. This tragedy deeply impacted the nation, leading to discussions about security, extremism, and the resilience of Norwegian society.
